                            Harfat was distressed by the exploitation of 
                            Anonymi 3765 and Anonymi 3766
                            by his kinsman Anonymi 3764. He does not approve of the great wealth of the estate
                            they inherited.
                         <a href="/803-13" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">event: </span>
                            When his slaves complained about 
                            Theodore 
                            giving all of his money away, he freed them.
                         <a href="/848-25" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">event: </span>
                            Sometime in the early 520s
                            Severus of Antioch sent a letter to 
                            John and 
                            John
                            on the subjects of Christian slaves sold by Jewish owners, fellowship with clergy who accept 
                            non-Chalcedonian theology but remain in communion with Chalcedonians, and the persecution of 
                            non-Chalcedonians.
                         <a href="/3107-44" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">event: </span>
                            Anonymi 3744 sold
                            Anonymous 3745 whom they had enslaved.
                         <a href="/3107-50" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">event: </span>Severus
                            advises Valeriena to encourage the virgins to an
                            ascetic life, suggesting their isolation from men, sharing common meals,
                            discouraging the owning of enslaved people, and emphasize physical
                            labour.  <a href="/3029-9" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><div class="citation"><h3>How to cite:</h3><span class="element">
